---
const techTools = [
    "JavaScript",
    "TypeScript",
    "React",
    "NextJs",
    "Astro",
    "Testing Library/Jest",
    "REST API's",
    "HTML",
    "CSS/Sass",
    "eslint",
    "StandardJS",
    "Figma",
];
---

<section
    class="container h-full mx-auto !max-w-7xl px-6 py-8 md:px-10 md:py-16"
>
    <header class="text-center mx-auto mb-12">
        <h5 class="italic text-xl text-blue-600 mb-2">Work experiences</h5>
        <h3 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl">
            <span class="font-bold">Working</span>
            for a great company
        </h3>
    </header>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-4">
        <div class="mb-10 md:mb-0">
            <h4 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-bold text-slate-700 mb-2">
                Web Designer & Front-end Developer
            </h4>
            <p class="italic font-semibold">Comercializadora ZEYMA SAS</p>
            <p>Medicine Distributor, Barranquilla (Colombia)</p>
            <p>Septembre 2020 - Present</p>

            <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-700 mt-4 mb-1">Tech Tools</h4>
            <div class="space-x-2 space-y-2 [text-wrap:balance]">
                {
                    techTools.map((tech) => (
                        <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-blue-50 px-2 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-blue-700 ring-1 ring-inset ring-blue-700/10 hover:ring-blue-500 transition-color duration-200">
                            {tech}
                        </span>
                    ))
                }
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-10">
            <article>
                <h5 class="uppercase text-md md:text-lg mb-2 font-bold">
                    WORK AND RESPONSABILITIES
                </h5>
                <ul class="ml-6 my-2 space-y-1 list-disc">
                    <li>
                        Design and implement new functionalities to existing
                        applications.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Maintenance of current applications. Fix error that
                        allow to increase the performance of webapps.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Train staff in the management of new functionalities.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Coordinate with different areas the required requests.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Optimize components in React for better performance.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Create applications with NodeJs that allows obtaining
                        data from the local database to regenerate custom
                        reports.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Maintenance of the application created in NodeJS in
                        charge of electronic invoicing.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </article>

            <article>
                <h5 class="uppercase text-md md:text-lg mb-2 font-bold">
                    KEY ACCOMPLISHMENTS
                </h5>
                <ul class="ml-6 my-2 space-y-2 list-disc">
                    <li>
                        Improved the database update to a webapp by reducing
                        update time from 5 minutes to 10 seconds, by using more
                        efficient techniques from the local database.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Improved the company efficiency by reducing delivery
                        time, using a webapp where clients can send purchases
                        orders to the offices with a real-time stock.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Improved company websiteâ€™s performance by increasing
                        fast loading from 5 sec to 1.5 sec, by implementing
                        astro techonology and lazy loading in all images.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </article>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
